   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>Windsor, a Londoner, was a loyal supporter of <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> and leader at the Foundery for
                  over forty years. He seems to have succeeded <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers0329.xml"/>Thomas Butts</persName> as the second
                  steward of the society, along with <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers0256.xml"/>William Briggs</persName>. <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> preached his funeral sermon on <date when="1790-02-07">Feb. 7,
                     1790</date>, describing him as 'a prudent, serious, diligent man, full of
                  mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy'. See
                  Stevenson, <hi rend="italic">City Road</hi>, 507–8.</p>
            
         
